Note:
XML to HIR Translator - Converts XML AST to Runa HIR

This file translates XML Abstract Syntax Trees into Runa's High-level
Intermediate Representation (HIR). This enables XML data to be processed
as native Runa data structures.

Translation Mapping:
- XML Element → Runa Dictionary with:
  - "_tag" key: element name (String)
  - "_attributes" key: Dictionary of attributes
  - "_children" key: List of child nodes
  - Optionally: attribute keys directly in dictionary
- XML Text → Runa String literal
- XML CDATA → Runa String literal (treated as text)
- XML Comment → Preserved as Dictionary with "_comment" key
- XML Processing Instruction → Preserved as Dictionary with "_pi" key

Features:
- Complete semantic preservation
- Attribute access as dictionary keys
- Mixed content support (text and elements)
- Nested element support
- Memory-safe translation
- Comment and PI preservation (optional)

Dependencies:
- xml_parser.runa (for XML AST)
- compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa (for HIR nodes)
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/xml/xml_parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Translation Context
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
XML translation needs the same first-error capture and source position as TOML/JSON, plus a boolean toggle for whether to preserve comments and processing instructions in the output - some callers want round-trip fidelity, others want a clean data-only view.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Five 8-byte fields: heap-allocated error_message pointer, has_error flag, current source line/column, and preserve_comments flag (0 by default, set by callers that want comments and PIs to survive translation).
@End Implementation

Type called "XMLToHIRContext":
    error_message as Integer    Note: Error message (if any)
    has_error as Integer        Note: Boolean: 1 if error occurred
    line as Integer             Note: Current line number
    column as Integer           Note: Current column number
    preserve_comments as Integer  Note: Boolean: preserve comments/PIs
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Context Creation and Destruction
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
A fresh context must default to "no error, no preserved comments" so callers wanting fidelity must explicitly set preserve_comments after construction; this safe default produces minimal HIR output.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate 40 bytes; null-check. Initialise error_message=0, has_error=0, line=0, column=0, preserve_comments=0.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_translation_context" returns Integer:
    Note: Create XML to HIR translation context

    Let context_size be 40  Note: XMLToHIRContext: 5 fields × 8 bytes
    Let context be proc allocate from Layout with context_size

    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Initialize context
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 0, 0   Note: error_message = null
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 8, 0   Note: has_error = false
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 16, 0  Note: line = 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 24, 0  Note: column = 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 32, 0  Note: preserve_comments = false

    Return context
End Process

@Reasoning:
The context owns its error_message buffer; teardown must release it to prevent the standard "translation failed and context discarded" leak path.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-check the context. Read the error_message pointer; if non-null deallocate. Deallocate the context block.
@End Implementation

Process called "destroy_translation_context" takes context as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Destroy translation context

    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Free error message if exists
    Let error_message be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    If error_message is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with error_message
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with context

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Error Handling
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Translation must record only the first error and own a copy of the message; allocating fresh storage decouples the message lifetime from the caller's buffer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Read existing error_message; if non-null free it. Measure new message length, allocate length+1 bytes, copy message bytes, null-terminate. Store at offset 0 and set has_error=1 at offset 8.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_translation_error" takes context as Integer, message as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set translation error message

    Let error_message be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    Note: Free previous error if exists
    If error_message is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with error_message
    End If

    Note: Copy error message
    Let msg_length be proc string_length from StringCore with message
    Let new_error be proc allocate from Layout with msg_length plus 1

    If new_error is not equal to 0:
        proc memory_copy from Layout with new_error, 0, message, 0, msg_length
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with new_error, msg_length, 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 0, new_error
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 8, 1  Note: has_error = true

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: XML Node to HIR Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
XML has six AST kinds (document, element, text, CDATA, comment, processing instruction); central dispatch lets each translator stay focused on one shape and shares position-update bookkeeping.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-check; record an error and return 0 on null. Read the node tag at offset 0 and the source line/column at offsets 40/48 into the context. Dispatch on tag to the matching translate_xml_* helper. Unknown tags record an error and return 0.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_xml_node_to_hir" takes context as Integer, xml_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate XML AST node to HIR node

    If xml_node is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Null XML node"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get node type and position
    Let node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with xml_node, 0
    Let line be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with xml_node, 40
    Let column be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with xml_node, 48

    Note: Update context position
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 16, line
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 24, column

    Note: Translate based on node type
    If node_type is equal to XML_DOCUMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_xml_document with context, xml_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to XML_ELEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_xml_element with context, xml_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to XML_TEXT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_xml_text with context, xml_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to XML_CDATA from Parser:
        Return proc translate_xml_cdata with context, xml_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to XML_COMMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_xml_comment with context, xml_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to XML_PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_xml_pi with context, xml_node
    End If

    proc set_translation_error with context, "Unknown XML node type"
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
The XML root document wraps the actual document element along with prologue PIs and comments; HIR should return the root element directly so consumers see the meaningful tree without having to peel one layer of envelope.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Read the children list at offset 32; error-out if null or empty. Walk children looking for the first child with tag XML_ELEMENT - that is the document element. Error-out if none found. Forward to translate_xml_element on that node.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_xml_document" takes context as Integer, xml_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate XML document to HIR

    Note: Get children list
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with xml_node, 32

    If children is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Document has no children"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with children

    If count is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Empty document"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Find root element (skip PIs and comments)
    Let index be 0
    Let root_element be 0

    While index is less than count:
        Let child be proc get_at from List with children, index
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to XML_ELEMENT from Parser:
            Set root_element to child
            Break
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    If root_element is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "No root element found"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Translate root element
    Return proc translate_xml_element with context, root_element
End Process

@Reasoning:
XML elements become Runa Dictionaries with reserved underscore-prefixed keys ("_tag", "_attributes", "_children") plus a "flat" copy of attributes as direct dictionary entries so Runa code can read attr.name without typing element["_attributes"]["name"].
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Build a HIR dictionary. Read element_name, attributes, and children from offsets 8/24/32. Insert "_tag" -> string literal of element_name. If attributes present, iterate keys: insert each into a fresh "_attributes" subdict and also into the outer dict directly. If children present and non-empty, recursively translate each child via translate_xml_node_to_hir, append non-null results to a list literal, attach under "_children".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(n) in attribute count + child count, plus recursive cost over all descendants; two HIR string allocations per attribute (one for "_attributes" subdict, one for direct dictionary access).
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "translate_xml_element" takes context as Integer, xml_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate XML element to HIR dictionary

    Note: Get element properties
    Let element_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with xml_node, 8
    Let attributes be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with xml_node, 24
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with xml_node, 32

    Note: Create HIR dictionary for element
    Let hir_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

    If hir_dict is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR dictionary"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add _tag key
    Let tag_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with element_name
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_tag", tag_value

    Note: Add attributes
    If attributes is not equal to 0:
        Note: Create attributes dictionary
        Let hir_attrs be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR
        Let attr_keys be proc keys from Dict with attributes

        If attr_keys is not equal to 0:
            Let attr_count be proc size from List with attr_keys
            Let attr_index be 0

            While attr_index is less than attr_count:
                Let attr_name be proc get_at from List with attr_keys, attr_index
                Let attr_value be proc get from Dict with attributes, attr_name

                Let hir_attr_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with attr_value
                proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_attrs, attr_name, hir_attr_value

                Note: Also add attribute directly to element dictionary for easy access
                Let hir_attr_value2 be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with attr_value
                proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, attr_name, hir_attr_value2

                Set attr_index to attr_index plus 1
            End While
        End If

        proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_attributes", hir_attrs
    End If

    Note: Add children
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let child_count be proc size from List with children

        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Let hir_children be proc create_hir_list_literal from HIR
            Let child_index be 0

            While child_index is less than child_count:
                Let child_node be proc get_at from List with children, child_index
                Let hir_child be proc translate_xml_node_to_hir with context, child_node

                If hir_child is not equal to 0:
                    proc add_list_element from HIR with hir_children, hir_child
                End If

                Set child_index to child_index plus 1
            End While

            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_children", hir_children
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_dict
End Process

@Reasoning:
XML text nodes carry their decoded character data (entity references resolved by the parser); lifting them straight into HIR string literals preserves content without further interpretation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Read the text value pointer at offset 16. Error-out if null. Wrap it in an HIR string literal.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_xml_text" takes context as Integer, xml_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate XML text to HIR string literal

    Note: Get text value
    Let text_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with xml_node, 16

    If text_value is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Text node has no value"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create HIR string literal
    Let hir_string be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with text_value

    If hir_string is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR string literal"
        Return 0
    End If

    Return hir_string
End Process

@Reasoning:
CDATA sections "<![CDATA[...]]>" exist in XML purely as an escape-bypass for character data; once the parser has stripped the delimiters they are functionally identical to text content, so HIR represents them as plain string literals.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Read the CDATA value pointer at offset 16; error-out if null. Wrap in an HIR string literal.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_xml_cdata" takes context as Integer, xml_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate XML CDATA to HIR string literal

    Note: Get CDATA value
    Let cdata_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with xml_node, 16

    If cdata_value is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "CDATA node has no value"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create HIR string literal
    Let hir_string be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with cdata_value

    If hir_string is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR string literal"
        Return 0
    End If

    Return hir_string
End Process

@Reasoning:
Comments carry semantic intent in some XML dialects (e.g., XSLT, configuration files); the preserve_comments flag lets callers opt in to round-trip fidelity while default callers strip comments to get clean data.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Read context.preserve_comments at offset 32; return 0 if disabled (skip the comment). Otherwise read the comment value at offset 16; if null return 0. Build an HIR dictionary with a single "_comment" entry holding the comment text as a string literal.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_xml_comment" takes context as Integer, xml_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate XML comment to HIR dictionary

    Let preserve_comments be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 32

    If preserve_comments is equal to 0:
        Return 0  Note: Skip comments if not preserving
    End If

    Note: Get comment value
    Let comment_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with xml_node, 16

    If comment_value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create dictionary with _comment key
    Let hir_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR
    Let hir_comment be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with comment_value

    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_comment", hir_comment

    Return hir_dict
End Process

@Reasoning:
Processing instructions like "<?xml-stylesheet ...?>" can carry critical document metadata; preserve_comments governs both comments and PIs since they share the same "structural metadata, not data" character.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Read context.preserve_comments; return 0 if disabled. Otherwise read the PI value at offset 16; if null return 0. Build an HIR dictionary with a single "_pi" entry holding the PI text as a string literal.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_xml_pi" takes context as Integer, xml_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate XML processing instruction to HIR dictionary

    Let preserve_comments be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 32

    If preserve_comments is equal to 0:
        Return 0  Note: Skip PIs if not preserving
    End If

    Note: Get PI value
    Let pi_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with xml_node, 16

    If pi_value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create dictionary with _pi key
    Let hir_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR
    Let hir_pi be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with pi_value

    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_pi", hir_pi

    Return hir_dict
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Top-Level Translation Function
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Public entry point hides the parse+translate+cleanup orchestration; failures at any stage bubble through a single error-reporting channel attached to the higher-level Translation context.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-check source_code; report and return 0. Create an internal translation context; on OOM report and return 0. Parse the source via Parser.parse_xml; on failure report and clean up. Recursively translate the AST root. On translation error forward the message to the outer context. Always destroy the internal context before returning.
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope:
Consumes untrusted XML source. The parser is expected to reject malformed XML; this translator only adds the HIR shape and cannot itself introduce parsing vulnerabilities.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "translate_xml_to_hir" takes source_code as Integer, translation_context as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate XML source code to Runa HIR

    If source_code is equal to 0:
        proc add_translation_error from Translation with translation_context, "Null source code"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create translation context
    Let context be proc create_translation_context

    If context is equal to 0:
        proc add_translation_error from Translation with translation_context, "Out of memory"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Parse XML
    Let xml_ast be proc parse_xml from Parser with source_code

    If xml_ast is equal to 0:
        proc add_translation_error from Translation with translation_context, "XML parse failed"
        proc destroy_translation_context from context
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Translate to HIR
    Let hir_root be proc translate_xml_node_to_hir with context, xml_ast

    Note: Check for translation errors
    Let has_error be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 8

    If has_error is equal to 1:
        Let error_msg be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0
        proc add_translation_error from Translation with translation_context, error_msg
        proc destroy_translation_context from context
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Cleanup
    proc destroy_translation_context from context

    Return hir_root
End Process

Note: End of XML to HIR Translator
